      <description>&lt;p&gt;On 26 March 2026 I will be speaking at the &lt;strong&gt;Data Management Summit London&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The panel will explore how financial institutions can move beyond fragmented data architectures to build unified data ecosystems that support accessibility, agility, and measurable business impact.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/DMS_2026.png&#34; alt=&#34;Data Management Summit London&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-takeaways&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Key Takeaways&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#key-takeaways&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Key observations from the panel discussion will be added here shortly after the event.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Topics expected to be discussed include:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
